1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with wireless sensor networks and proposes an energy efficient routing protocol for communication, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the transmission of binary information in a cooperative spectrum sensing environment, which involves information theory concepts. 
3. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper may involve security issues related to spectrum sensing in cognitive radio networks, which falls under the scope of cryptography and security. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes an intelligent decision-making routing method, which involves control and system theory concepts. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper may involve the use of AI techniques for intelligent decision making in the proposed routing protocol.
